See the file doc/goals.doc for a description of the overall goals,
	and the goals for this release.

See the file doc/ports.doc for the status of ports to various systems.

See the file TODO for identified tasks / wish list.

Changes from "alpha" distribution;
	Now portable!!
		Has run on 6 different Un*x systems (see doc/ports.doc).

		gendata.sno now creates init_data.h
			which initializes resident data at runtime.

		The only architectural assumption is that
			sizeof(long) == sizeof(float)
			(see include/types.h)

	DCMP() now done inline (did profiling).

	genc.sno runs 30% faster!

	descriptors are now "packed" using bit fields
		(now 8 bytes rather than 12)
		string length "limited" to 2^24 bytes,
		all other objects limited to 2^21 descriptors
			see types.h for discussion of sizes.

Status;
	All features on SNOBOL4 are implemented,
		including LOAD() (see doc/load.doc),
		EXCEPT for processing of arithmetic exceptions.

	May run slowly;
		genc.sno itself runs "only" 7x slower than under
		Catspaw SPARC (Macro) SPITBOL.  This is a respectable
		ratio for the two implementations!

		However programs which make extensive use of matching
		may run much slower.

		The pattern scanner and some pattern matching routines
		get split up into many small, mutually recusrsive
		routines!! gcc inlining may resolve this.

I/O;

	named files can be opened by supplying an optional fourth
	argument to INPUT() and OUTPUT(), like in Catspaw SNOBOL4.

	input is padded with spaces out to the default record length (80).
	&TRIM defaults to 1, so any trailing spaces are lost on input.

	by default INPUT is attached to unit 5, and standard input.
	by default OUTPUT is attached to unit 6, and standard output.
	by default PUNCH is attached to unit 7, and standard error!!!

Command line args;

	snobol4 [ options ... ] [ files ... ]

	-b
		Toggle startup banner output (by default on).

	-d NNN
		Have dynamic region contain space for NNN descriptors
		default is 25000.

	-k
		Run programs with compilation errors

	-l
		Reenable listing to OUTPUT. default is -UNLIST
		-l means '-LIST LEFT'

	-r
		Continue reading INPUT from input file(s) after END
		label.  otherwise INPUT defaults (back) to stdin after
		compilation.

	-s
		Toggle termination statistics (by default on).

To build;

select a suitable config file (see doc/ports.doc) from the config
directory, and link to config.h;

	ln -s config/sunos4.h config.h
	make

The tar does not contain any binaries; THEY SHOULD NOT BE NEEDED
(unless you touch the source files) As all generated files are
provided.  The generated files are NOT system dependant!!!
